Coffee is the second most consumed beverage in the world after tea, and is an important global crop ( Murthy & Naidu 2012 ). Coffee is grown in over 80 countries, serving as the main source of income for farmers in many of them ( Los Santos-Briones & Hernández-Sotomayor 2006 ). The top three coffee-producing countries are Brazil , Colombia and Vietnam (Lemma & Megersa. 2021). China is also one of the largest coffee producing countries, and its production is rapidly increasing (
Zhang et al. 2014
) with Yunnan Province accounting for more than 90% of coffee production in China ( Neilson & Wang 2019 ). Fungal infections have significant impacts on the production of coffee (
Adhikari et al. 2020
). Endophytic and saprobic fungi in coffee have also attracted attention as they can improve the quality of coffee while also acting as biocontrol agents to prevent and treat coffee diseases (
Angélico et al. 2017
,
Botrel et al. 2018
). Approximately 136 endophytes, 30 saprobes and 297 pathogens have been reported from coffee (
Lu et al. 2021
).
